news.title: Enforcement directorate arrests Heera Constructions' MD in money laundering case
news.para: According to sources, Abdul Rasheed alias Heera Babu was produced at Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) court in Kochi on Tuesday. Rasheed has been sent to ED custody for four days till Friday.

news.title: Kolkata: Quick nod to building plans on plots up to seven cottahs from January 2024
news.para: According to a KMC official, necessary preparations are being made to make the new system user friendly before rolling it out.

news.title: Falsely named in duping case by Samir Kochhar & Varun Bangera: Architects
news.para: Kochhar and Bangera had filed a complaint with Andheri police on November 21 alleging that the architects had duped them of around Rs 1 crore paid as total token amount for one flat each in the under-construction Bandra (West) building.

news.title: WeWork appoints Claudio Hidalgo as COO
news.para: Hidalgo served as the company's COO Americas between June and November this year, and was COO Latin America from April 2020 to August 2022. He succeeds Anthony Yazbeck, who stepped down from his role in October.

news.title: Geo-tagging of properties mandatory to avail property tax exemption in Delhi: MCD
news.para: If any taxpayer fails to geo-tag their properties by 31 January, they will not be able to avail 10 per cent rebate on lump sum advance payment of tax in the next financial year by June 30, it said.

news.title: Seller's PAN-Aadhaar not linked? Pay 20% TDS on property purchase
news.para: According to the provisions of the Income-Tax Act, the buyer of any property worth Rs 50 lakh or above must pay 1% TDS to the central government and 99% of the total cost to the seller, who can later claim it as credit.

news.title: Oberoi Realty completes acquisition of 6.4 acres land in Thane for Rs 196 crore
news.para: In May 2023, the company had entered into a memorandum of understanding with NRB Bearings (NRB) for acquiring the lands located at Pokhran Road 2, Thane, Maharashtra, together with structures thereon.

news.title: IWG resumes dividends, eyes $1 billion in medium-term profit
news.para: Switzerland-headquartered IWG, which owns the Spaces and Regus brands, has said it is looking to acquire more of collapsed rival WeWork's sites on expectations of strong demand.

news.title: Dalmia Cement (Bharat) appoints Puneet Yadu Dalmia as MD & CEO
news.para: The board also approved the appointment of Mahendra Singhi as strategic advisor to managing director & CEO with effect from December 9, 2023. Singhi will also act as non-executive non-independent director of Dalmia Cement (Bharat).

news.title: Kochi Metro to get Rs 24 crore more for phase-II works
news.para: Earlier the state government sanctioned Rs 354.57 crore for the preparatory works, including land acquisition for the 11.2km long Pink Line of Kochi Metro.

news.title: Byju’s founder Raveendran pledges homes to raise funds for staff salaries
news.para: The company is fighting to keep afloat amid financial pressures, including a legal battle with creditors over a missed interest payment on a $1.2 billion term loan. Raveendran has raised personal debts of $400 million and plowed back $800 million into the company.

news.title: Byju's reducing real estate footprint, vacates two offices in Bengaluru
news.para: The terminated office assets include 550,000 sq ft in Kalyani Tech Park in Whitefield and 70,000 sq ft in IBC Knowledge Park, people aware of the matter said. Both these assets were given up between 2022 and 2023.

news.title: Ambuja Cements completes acquisition of Sanghi Industries at an enterprise value of Rs 5,185 crore
news.para: With the acquisition funded entirely through internal accruals, Ambuja Cements holds a controlling stake of 54.51% in Sanghi Industries. It increases ACL's consolidated capacity to 74.6 MTPA from 68.5 MTPA.

news.title: Gujarat government discontinues 50% discount in land allotment
news.para: The AMC standing committee at a meeting in August, had approved this amendment, which overrules its September 2022 resolution that had granted GETCO, a 4,900sq m plot in Gota for a substation at a discounted rate.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: City Plaza flat owners to move HC over structures' stability issues
news.para: Recently, the city corporation cancelled as many as 84 building numbers of commercial and residential buildings of the City Plaza building at Ulloor after concerns were raised over the stability of the structure.

news.title: DTCP tightens checks on squatters, eight buildings razed in Saraswati Kunj
news.para: Officials said these houses were constructed without taking permission or getting building plans approved. Any kind of construction in the licensed colony is banned due to ongoing litigation.

news.title: Income tax departments raids GeeKen's offices in NCR, Mumbai & Chennai
news.para: Led by income tax commissioner Amanpreet Kaur, multiple teams of around 100 officials in total have been carrying out searches in GeeKen’s offices and showrooms in Noida, Delhi, Chandigarh, Chennai and Mumbai since Friday.

news.title: Over 340 proposals cleared till Nov 16 to complete stalled real estate projects: Government
news.para: "As of November 16, 2023, under SWAMIH, 342 proposals aggregating to Rs 37,554 crore have been approved and this will benefit around 2,18,699 homebuyers and unlock projects worth Rs 94,367 crore," the minister said.

news.title: Infra.Market divests 10% stake in RDC Concrete to raise $20 million
news.para: Current fund raise has closed at a valuation of approximately US $225 million. RDC Concrete is expected to have a revenue of Rs 2,000 crore by the end of FY24. It expects to have around 180 ready-mix concrete plants by the end of FY25.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises to jointly develop four acres project in Mysuru
news.para: The developable area of the project will be about 0.40 million sq ft with a gross development value (GDV) of Rs 300 crore. Brigade Group recently launched a residential project - Brigade Sanctuary, spread across 14 acres in Bengaluru.
